  "description": "A6 associative / multi-hop corpus: linked chains a->b->c (and a->b->c->d) seeded into the Hebbian co-activation graph by co-activating ONLY adjacent atoms. The query is the chain head; the gold answer is the chain tail, which is reachable only transitively through the middle node(s). Chain atoms are on distinct sub-topics so head<->tail vector similarity is low and the score is attributable to the multi-hop graph walk, not single-vector similarity. Distractor chains and isolated noise atoms widen the candidate pool. Each probe has exactly one gold id, so scoring is fully programmatic (no judge).",
